"narrative": {
"appearance": "Tall and strikingly composed, Goran Varus retains the refined features and aristocratic bearing of his High Elf heritage, now overlaid with the chilling pallor and unsettling stillness of the undead. His eyes are keen and an unnatural, icy blue, perpetually scanning the dark tunnel for any lapse in 'flawless order.' He wears tailored, high-quality garments that allow for maximum movement, likely in deep, rich colors appropriate for an overseer, but they are invariably dirtied with the grime of the deep mining line. His bloodforged items (mantle, bracers, and ring) pulse with a subtle, dark crimson light, a visible sign of the necrotic power feeding his Queen's war machine.",
"background": "Once a renowned High Elf architect in Westphal, Goran traded the intricate work of stone and spire for the dark, ruthless discipline of undeath. Remade into a Blueblood Vampire by his sire, he now applies his meticulous intellect and relentless pursuit of perfection to a monstrous task: overseeing the dozens-of-miles-long mining line beneath Castle Bloodforge. His domain is a world of crushing rock, flickering shadows, and weary thralls, all working to extract and refine the ore that feeds the Queen's bloodsteel forges for her planned war machine.",
