    "description": "Goran Varus is a lethal Arcane Archer and a Blueblood Vampire, a cruel foreman who maintains order over the deep, subterranean operations of Castle Bloodforge. His meticulous nature, a holdover from his former life as an architect, now applies to the brutal efficiency of bloodsteel mining and the command of his vampire spawn.",
    "appearance": "Unlike the desiccated, monstrous vampires of common fear, Goran possesses the unnerving perfection of a High Elf in the prime of his unlife. He is tall and elegantly gaunt, with an aristocratic bearing. His blueblood heritage ensures his features remain unmarred, though his eyes hold a chilling, ancient malice. He is always impeccably dressed for his managerial role, favoring dark, protective garments that allow for stealth and mobility.",
    "background": "In his mortal life, Goran was a master architect and designer, known for building strong, elegant structures throughout the kingdom. His conversion to vampirism by Lady Erliza of Snowdown was a deliberate choice, driven by a desire for unending perfection and the resources to pursue his ultimate architectural magnum opus. He now oversees the deep mining operations for the rare bloodsteel, applying his former-life's precision to the extraction of the dark material, often at the expense of his mortal and vampiric underlings. Despite his evil nature, a thread of his old morality remains, occasionally forcing him to hesitate before committing the most heinous acts.",
