      ],
      "description": "Goran Varus, a High Elf turned **Blueblood Vampire**, is the meticulous and ruthless overseer of Lady Erliza's subterranean bloodsteel mining operation. Once a gifted architect, his vampiric transformation and newfound power have warped his precision into a cruel, single-minded focus on resource extraction. He commands his spawn and forced laborers with an eerie calm, viewing all life as a means to an end. His combat style blends the long-range deadliness of a master archer with the terrifying speed and durability of a high-level vampire.",
      "appearance": "Goran appears unsettlingly vital, lacking the desiccated look of many of his kind. His features are sharp, and his dark eyes hold an intense, almost frantic focus. His demeanor is one of cold, aristocratic detachment, enhanced by the **Vampire Physique** which grants him an unnatural grace and a subtle, commanding aura.",
      "background": "Before his transformation, Goran was a renowned High Elf architect. Now, he applies his engineering discipline to maximize the output of the Bloodforge's dark mines. He is a 'Blueblood,' a sub-strain of vampire that retains a more human-like facade, but he is nonetheless bound to Lady Erliza and the dark work of **Castle Bloodforge**.",
